text.__SUMMARY__: Cuming's blind snake (Ramphotyphlops cumingii) is a species of snake in the family Typhlopidae. The species is endemic to the Philippines.
text.Etymology: The specific name, cumingii, is in honor of English conchologist and botanist Hugh Cuming.
text.Geographic range: In the Philippines, it is found in Bohol, Marinduque, Mindanao, Negros, Panay, and Polillo.
text.Further reading: Gray JE (1845). Catalogue of the Specimens of Lizards in the Collection of the British Museum. London: Trustees of the British Museum. (Edward Newman, printer). xxviii + 289 pp. (Onychophis cumingii, new species, p. 133).
